Name: Adonis
Full Description, Information, or Custom: This painting depicts a young man enthroned partially dressed but displaying his manhood. The privileged status of a man is evident in his posturing. This man represents the new twenty-first century “David”.

Name: Adonis 2
Full Description, Information, or Custom: In a series of paintings using the torsos of men and women the artist shows the beauty of the human body, our touch of the Divine. At the same time I suggest that we are subjected by our society to dismemberment and violence because of sin. Underlining beauty are the terrible struggles man and woman must undergo.

Name: Alhambra
Full Description, Information, or Custom: “The Alhambra is a palace and fortress complex located in Granada, Andalusia, Spain. It is one of the most famous monuments of Islamic architecture and one of the best-preserved palaces of the historic Islamic world, in addition to containing notable examples of Spanish Renaissance architecture.” Wikipedia In this work I used many of the sketches and watercolors that I created while in Granada.

Name: Apocalypse 1
Full Description, Information, or Custom: One of two paintings with horsemen of the apocalypse.

Name: Apocalypse 2
Full Description, Information, or Custom: One of two paintings with horsemen of the apocalypse. Created because of the dynamic relationship between the horsemen, their steeds and the viewer.

Name: Assisi Basilica of St. Francis
Full Description, Information, or Custom: With vivid colors this rendition of the famous Convent/basilica in Assisi was part of the “Road to Rome” series that was exhibited in 4 major venues; Pope John-Paul II Cultural Center, Washington D.C., Catholic Art Museum, New York City, Marshal Fields, Chicago, Il.

Name: Basilica & Fountain, Saint Benoit Sur Loire, France
Bell Tower of San Diego, California
Full Description, Information, or Custom: From the California Mission series featured in the book; An Uncommon Mission. And displayed at the Getty Gallery of the Los Angeles Public Library, The Historical Museum of Santa Barbara, the History Museum of San Diego and the Fresno Fine Art Museum. These exhibits featured paintings and watercolors of all 21 missions in California.

Name: Bob Shairqi
Full Description, Information, or Custom: The series of paintings and watercolors from cities and landscapes in the region of the Middle East; Constantinople to Cairo. This piece represents the biblical passage where Paul escapes from violence and possible death by being lowered from a house on the wall in a basket.

Name: Cahors, France, From Henry IV's Courtyard
Full Description, Information, or Custom: “Painting the Pilgrimage; from the Paris to Compostela”. Paintings and watercolors were exhibited at the Naples Philharmonic Museum of Art. I painted the watercolors and sketched while traveling from Paris to Compostela in Spain. The most famous pilgrimage route for Christians since the 9th Century. Pilgrims have used many different modes of transport to make this long and arduous trek, often from places as far away as Sweden or Eastern Europe.

Name: California Missions, San Fernando

Name: The Cavalier and His Lady
Full Description, Information, or Custom: One of my most loved pieces. This painting was created in Rome for an exhibit in Paris at the UNESCO Museum and was the centerpiece of that exhibition. The piece has several layers of meaning; A Knight on horseback embracing a young woman walking; metaphor for the “pericorisis”. Which is the understanding ancient theologians had of the relationship between the persons of the Trinity. The viewer is wrapped in the circular movement of the man, woman and horse. This piece was inspired by the artists love of classical ballet as seen in the woman being swept up by her partner into an aerial movement. She is seen as being “en point”.

Name: Chartres Upper & Lower Village
Full Description, Information, or Custom: This French city is much loved for its cathedral and the many historic building reminiscent of the late medieval period when Chartres was a famous center of learning. In this painting I have shown the apse, façade and the treasury of the cathedral but also the lower medieval village where I had an apartment while studying for my degree in Paris.

Name: Church of Saint Ambrose, Milan, Italy
Church of Saint Bartholomew, Aleppo, Syria
Full Description, Information, or Custom: This painting in from the series “Shrines, Churches and Mosques; from Constantinople to Cairo”. This is a parish church in the center of Aleppo and created just prior to the destruction of this great city in the Syrian war. Paintings from this series are often of buildings that no longer exist.

Name: Church of Saint George
Full Description, Information, or Custom: Although badly damaged by the recent war, this was one of many Christian churches in the ancient Silk Road center of commerce.

Name: Church of the Nativity, Bethlehem, Apse & Facade
Full Description, Information, or Custom: Painting inspired by the sketches of this most ancient of basilicas in Christendom. This Roman building was spared the destruction of all the other great Roman basilicas by the Persians in the 6th century. The exterior elements of this building reflect the many different architectural styles which make up this fortress like church complex. The painting shows both the facade and fort like building facing the Bethlehem Plaza but also it’s gothic style apse. The plaza is made up of two carpets from Iranian weavers designs.

Name: Church Plaza on Patmos
Full Description, Information, or Custom: Painting of the site where St. John the Evangelist wrote the Book of Revelation. The site reflects the architecture inspired by the fortresses built by the Knights of Malta.

Name: Dowager Empress Young Cixi
Full Description, Information, or Custom: Painting showing the last important Dowager Empress of China as a young Courtesan. While being ruthless in real life she was chosen as Empress because of her courtly ways as a young woman. In this portrait she is enthroned on a beautiful fan backed wooden chair (which I found near my studio}. This chair inspired me to paint a number of works from Chinese history. Pictures like ‘Dowger…” ‘Tea for Cixi’ and a painting of the “last Emperor of China Puyi” the chair figures prominently in all of the paintings from the year 2022.

Name: Philosophical Garden 1
Medium / Material: Qauche and Sumi Ink on Paper
Full Description, Information, or Custom:
This series is based on using the spiritual shrine as the central circular figure and residing on the earthlike structure from which springs suggestions of flora. In my mind this piece and the whole series suggests something ethereal but central to our human experience.

This painting using gouache and Sumi ink is one in a series of pieces where I explore the relationships between upper and lower worlds; psychological, seedling from root to air, a garden in bloom with a shining sun.

Name: Qin Shi Huang
Full Description, Information, or Custom: I was inspired by ancient Chinese painting for this work and translated their forms into a contemporary setting.  I have used Gold Leaf for Qin Shi's robe and the throne is one to be found in each of the paintings in this series.

Name: St. Augustine Priory, Bahamas, Side View
Full Description, Information, or Custom:
In a series of watercolor and ink paintings on paper I was working in the Bahamas at the St. John's Priory St. Augustine.

The rich saturated colors reflect the intensity of light on the buildings and vegetation.

‍

Name: Sentinels of Fire
Full Description, Information, or Custom: Using ancient icon symbolism, I have translated these details into geometric forms.  This painting is particulary arresting because of the blue background contrasting with the rich reds

Name: Sentinel of Fire: Covenant
Full Description, Information, or Custom: One of my paintings that I have kept since it was shown in 1989. This series reflect my visual interpretation of the Divine. Using the circle as an infinite form suggesting through the use of color both passion and radiance. The orb rests on a feminine form proposing the idea of God as feminine force.

Name: Sentinels of Fire: Gold
Full Description, Information, or Custom: Painting is made rich with the golden impasto used on the surface.  The band of red gives the impression of a division taking place by the powerful magma eminating from it's core.  I find this a very haunting piece because of the rich contrasts.
